name: Unload
description: WorldEvent.Unload is fired when Minecraft unloads a world. This event is fired when a world is unloaded in Minecraft#loadWorld(WorldClient, String), MinecraftServer#deleteWorldAndStopServer(), MinecraftServer#stopServer(), DimensionManager#unloadWorlds(Hashtable ), ForgeInternalHandler#onDimensionUnload(Unload). This event is not Cancelable . This event does not have a result. HasResult This event is fired on the MinecraftForge#EVENT_BUS .
